## Installation

Homepage was deployed using Docker Compose on `pi-main`.

Basic setup:

```bash
sudo mkdir -p /opt/stacks/homepage/config
cd /opt/stacks/homepage
sudo nano docker-compose.yml
docker compose up -d
```


# Homepage Dashboard

## Overview

This folder contains the Docker Compose setup for my self-hosted Homepage dashboard.

Homepage is used as a central dashboard for my homelab. Instead of trying to remember every service URL, I can use this dashboard to organize links to the tools and applications running in my environment.

## Why I Added This

As my homelab grows, it becomes harder to keep track of every service, port, and web interface.

This dashboard helps me keep everything in one place, such as:

- Portainer
- Jellyfin
- Nextcloud
- Traefik
- Grafana
- Prometheus
- Other future services

This also makes the homelab feel more organized and easier to manage.

## Folder Location

On the Raspberry Pi, this stack is stored at:

```bash
/opt/stacks/homepage